<English>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<French>: Emblème de la 702e Escadrille aéronavale. La 702 a été formée le 16 juillet 1936, et pendant la majeure partie de sa vie opérationnelle, elle a piloté divers avions de reconnaissance. Après avoir été réformée en 1978, elle a servi d'unité d'entraînement pour l'exploitation et la maintenance du Westland Lynx, avant d'être absorbée par le 815 NAS en 2014. Le marquage est la tête stylisée d'un Lynx, dérivé de l'insigne de l'escadron. Le marquage a été placé sur plusieurs de leurs hélicoptères Lynx, et a été positionné à droite de la fenêtre latérale.
<Italian>: Stemma della Squadriglia Aerea Navale N° 702. La 702 venne formata il 16 luglio 1936 e nella maggior parte della sua vita operativa, utilizzò vari aerei da ricognizione. Dopo essere riformata nel 1978, servirono come unità di addestramento mantenendo la "Westland Lynx", prima di essere assorbita dalla 815 NAS nel 2014. Lo stemma era una testa di Lince stilizzata derivata dalla toppa della squadriglia. Era posto su molti elicotteri Lynx, a destra del finestrino laterale.
<German>: Ein Abzeichen des 702 Naval Air Squadron. Die 702 wurde am 16. Juli 1936 gegründet und flog die meiste Zeit ihres frühen Einsatzes verschiedene Aufklärungsflugzeuge. Nach ihrer Umstrukturierung 1978 diente sie als Ausbildungseinheit für den Betrieb und die Wartung der Westland Lynx, bevor sie 2014 in die 815 NAS eingegliedert wurde. Das Abzeichen sind der stilisierte Kopf eines Luchs, eine Variante des Geschwader-Abzeichens. Das Abzeichen wurde auf mehreren ihrer Hubschrauber des Typs Lynx angebracht und befand sich rechts neben dem Seitenfenster.
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón Aeronaval 702. El 702 se formó el 16 de Julio de 1936, y durante la mayor parte de su vida operativa temprana voló con varios aviones de reconocimiento. Tras ser reformado en 1978, sirvió como unidad de entrenamiento operando y manteniendo el Westland Lynx, antes de ser absorbido por el 815 NAS en 2014. La marca es la cabeza estilizada de un Lince, derivada de la insignia del escuadrón. El distintivo se colocó en varios de sus helicópteros Lynx, a la derecha de la ventanilla lateral.
<Russian>: Эмблема "Рысь", 815 эскадрилья ВВС Королевского флота Британии
<Polish>: Emblemat Eskadry Lotnictwa Morskiego nr 702. Eskadra została sformowana 16 lipca 1936 roku i przez większość wczesnego okresu operacyjnego latała na różnych samolotach rozpoznawczych. Po ponownym sformowaniu w 1978 roku służyła jako jednostka szkoleniowa, obsługując i utrzymując śmigłowce Westland Lynx, zanim została wchłonięta przez Eskadrę 815 NAS w 2014 roku. Emblematem była stylizowana głowa rysia, wywodząca się z herbu eskadry. Znak ten był umieszczany na kilku śmigłowcach Lynx, znajdując się po prawej stronie okna bocznego.
<Czech>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<Turkish>: 702 Deniz Hava Filosunun amblemi. 702 16 Temmuz 1936'da kuruldu ve ilk operasyonel yaşamının büyük bölümünde çeşitli keşif uçakları uçurdu. 1978'de yeniden yapılandırıldıktan sonra, 2014'te 815 NAS'a dahil edilmeden önce Westland Lynx'i işleten ve bakımını yapan bir eğitim birimi olarak hizmet vermiştir. İşaret, filo rozetinin türevi olan stilize bir Lynx başıdır. İşaret Lynx helikopterlerinin birçoğunun üzerine yerleştirilmiş ve yan pencerenin sağında konumlandırılmıştır.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t海\t军\t舰\t队\t航\t空\t兵\t第 702 海\t航\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t第 702 海\t航\t中\t队\t成\t立\t于 1936 年 7 月 16 日，\t早\t期\t主\t要\t装\t备\t各\t型\t侦\t察\t机\t执\t行\t侦\t查\t任\t务。\t中\t队\t于 1978 年\t重\t组\t为\t训\t练\t单\t位，\t主\t要\t装\t备\t韦\t斯\t特\t兰\t“山\t猫”\t直\t升\t机，\t随\t后\t在 2014 年\t并\t入\t第 815 海\t航\t中\t队。\t徽\t标\t采\t用\t了\t中\t队\t纹\t章\t图\t样\t中\t标\t志\t性\t的\t山\t猫\t头\t为\t主\t体，\t主\t要\t见\t于\t部\t队\t下\t属\t“山\t猫”\t直\t升\t机\t的\t机\t身\t舷\t窗\t右\t侧。
<Japanese>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<Portuguese>: Um emblema do 702 Esquadrão Aéreo Naval. O 702 foi formado em 16 de julho de 1936 e, durante a maior parte de sua vida operacional, voou em várias aeronaves de reconhecimento. Depois de serem reformados em 1978, serviram como unidade de treinamento operando e mantendo o Westland Lynx, antes de serem absorvidos pelo 815 NAS em 2014. A marcação é a cabeça estilizada de um Lynx, derivado do distintivo do esquadrão. A marcação foi colocada em vários de seus helicópteros Lynx e posicionada à direita da janela lateral.
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 702-ї морської авіаційної ескадрильї. 702-а була сформований 16-го липня 1936 року, і протягом більшої частини свого раннього терміну служби літала на різних літаках-розвідниках. Після реформування в 1978 році вони слугували навчальним підрозділом, який керував і обслуговував Westland Lynx, перш ніж увійти до складу 815 NAS у 2014 році. Позначкою є стилізована голова рисі, похідна від значка ескадрильї. Маркування було розміщено на кількох їхніх вертольотах Lynx праворуч від бічного вікна.
<Serbian>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Haditengerészeti Légierő 815. haditengerészeti repülőszázadának emblémája.
<Korean>: 제702해군항공비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 1936년 7월 16일에 창설된 이 비행대는 초기에 다양한 정찰기를 운용하였습니다. 1978년에 재편성된 이 비행대는 웨스트랜드 링스를 운용하는 훈련대로 편성되어 있다가 2014년, 제815비행대와 통합되었습니다. 이곳은 비행대의 배지에서 파생된 스라소니(Lynx)의 머리가 마킹되어 있었습니다. 해당 마킹은 수 대의 링스 헬리콥터의  우측면 창문에 적용되어 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: "Lynx" emblem, No. 815 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Romanian>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<TChinese>: An emblem of 702 Naval Air Squadron. 702 formed on July 16th 1936, and for the majority of its early operational life flew various reconnaissance aircraft. After being reformed in 1978, they served as a training unit operating and maintaining the Westland Lynx, before being absorbed into 815 NAS in 2014. The marking is the stylized head of a Lynx, derivative of squadron's badge. The marking was placed on several of their Lynx helicopters, and was positioned to the right of the side window.
<HChinese>: "Lynx" emblem, No. 815 Naval Air Squadron, Fleet Air Arm of the Royal Navy
<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng của Sư đoàn Không quân Hải quân 702. Sư đoàn 702 được thành lập vào ngày 16 tháng 7 năm 1936, và trong phần lớn thời kỳ hoạt động đầu của nó, họ đã sử dụng nhiều loại máy bay trinh sát khác nhau. Sau khi tái hình thành vào năm 1978, họ phục vụ như một đơn vị đào tạo vận hành và bảo dưỡng máy bay Westland Lynx, trước khi được hợp nhất vào Sư đoàn Không quân Hải quân 815 vào năm 2014. Biểu tượng là hình đầu của một con Linh, phát triển từ huy hiệu của sư đoàn. Biểu tượng này được đặt trên một số trực thăng Lynx của họ, và được đặt bên phải của cửa sổ bên.

<English>: Emblem of 1st Group, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Long Range Reconnaissance Group) 120. The emblem displays the skull of a Moose with the distinctive thick antlers. A simplification of the original emblem, this marking was painted to the side of the nose on the Ju 88 aircraft in use with the group, just in front of the cockpit.
<French>: Emblème du 1e groupe, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (groupe de reconnaissance à longue portée) 120. L'emblème affiche le crane d'un élan avec les épais bois distinctifs. Une simplification de l'emblème original, ce marquage était peint sur le côté du nez des avions Ju 88 en usage dans le groupe, juste devant le cockpit.
<Italian>: Stemma del 1° Gruppo Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Gruppo di Ricognizione a Lungo Raggio) 120. Lo stemma rappresentava un teschio di alce con le corna spesse. Una semplificazione dello stemma originale che veniva dipinto sui lati del muso dei Ju 88 operativi nel gruppo, appena avanti alla cabina di pilotaggio.
<German>: Abzeichen der 1. Staffel, Fernaufklärungsgruppe 120. Das Abzeichen zeigt den Schädel eines Elches mit dem charakteristischen dicken Geweih. Dieses Abzeichen, das eine Vereinfachung des ursprünglichen Abzeichens darstellt, wurde seitlich auf die Nase der bei der Gruppe eingesetzten Ju 88-Flugzeuge gemalt, direkt vor dem Cockpit.
<Spanish>: Emblema del 1º Grupo, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Grupo de Reconocimiento de Largo Alcance) 120. El emblema muestra el cráneo de un alce con la gruesa cornamenta distintiva. Esta marca, simplificación del emblema original, se pintó en el morro de los aviones Ju 88 del grupo, justo delante de la cabina.
<Polish>: Emblemat 1. Grupy, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Grupa Rozpoznania Dalekiego Zasięgu) 120. Emblemat przedstawia czaszkę łosia z charakterystycznymi grubymi porożami. Jest to uproszczenie oryginalnego emblematu, który był malowany na boku nosa samolotów Ju 88 używanych przez grupę, tuż przed kabiną.
<Czech>: Emblém 1. skupiny Fernaufklärungsgruppe (průzkumná skupina s dlouhým doletem) 120. Znak zobrazuje lebku losa s charakteristickým hustým parožím. Toto označení, které je zjednodušením původního znaku, bylo na letounech Ju 88 používaných u skupiny namalováno na boční stranu přídě, těsně před pilotní kabinu.
<Turkish>: 1. Grup, Fernaufklärungsgruppe (Uzun Menzilli Keşif Grubu) 120'nin amblemi. Amblemde kendine özgü kalın boynuzları olan bir Geyik kafatası görülmektedir. Orijinal amblemin sadeleştirilmiş hali olan bu işaret, grupta kullanılan Ju 88 uçaklarında burnun yan tarafına, kokpitin hemen önüne boyanmıştır.
<Chinese>: 德\t国\t空\t军\t第 120 远\t程\t侦\t察\t联\t队\t第 1 中\t队\t后\t期\t徽\t标。\t图\t案\t为\t驼\t鹿\t头\t骨\t以\t及\t其\t标\t志\t性\t的\t分\t叉\t鹿\t角。\t该\t徽\t标\t是\t原\t始\t设\t计\t的\t简\t化\t版\t本，\t见\t于\t该\t中\t队\t装\t备\t的 Ju 88 座\t舱\t前\t方。

<Chinese>: 第 400 战\t斗\t机\t联\t队\t第 7 中\t队\t徽\t标
<TChinese>: 第 400 戰\t鬥\t機\t聯\t隊\t第 7 中\t隊\t徽\t標

<English>: An emblem used by 7th Group, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Like several late-war markings this emblem was never officially approved to represent 7th group, but was nevertheless placed on the nose of their Me 163 fighters. The emblem depicts Baron Münchhausen riding a bottle rocket, making it quite an appropriate motif.
<French>: Un emblème utilisé par le 7e groupe, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Comme plusieurs marquages tardifs de la guerre, cet emblème n'était jamais approuvé officiellement pour représenter le 7e groupe, mais était néanmoins placé sur le nez de leurs chasseurs Me 163. L'emblème représente le Baron Münchhausen chevauchant une bouteille-roquette, ce qui en fait un motif tout à fait approprié.
<Italian>: Uno stemma usato dal 7° gruppo, Jagdgeschwader (Stormo Caccia) 400. Come molti altri stemmi di tardo conflitto, questo non venne mai ufficialmente approvato per rappresentare il 7° gruppo ma posto sotto il muso dei loro caccia Me 163. Raffigurava il Barone Münchhausen che cavalcava un razzo facendolo apparire come inappropriato.
<German>: Ein Abzeichen, das von der 7. Staffel des Jagdgeschwaders 400 verwendet wurde. Wie viele andere Abzeichen aus der späten Phase des Krieges wurde auch dieses Abzeichen nie offiziell für die 7. Staffel genehmigt, wurde aber dennoch auf der Nase ihrer Me 163-Jagdflugzeuge angebracht. Das Abzeichen zeigt Baron Münchhausen, der auf einer Flaschenrakete reitet, und ist damit ein recht passendes Motiv.
<Spanish>: Emblema utilizado por el 7º Grupo, Jagdgeschwader (Ala de Caza) 400. Al igual que varias marcas de finales de la guerra, este emblema nunca fue aprobado oficialmente para representar al 7º grupo, pero sin embargo se colocó en el morro de sus cazas Me 163. El emblema representa al Barón Münchhausen montado en una botella cohete, lo que lo convierte en un motivo bastante apropiado.
<Polish>: Emblemat używany przez 7. Grupę, Jagdgeschwader (Skrzydło Myśliwskie) 400. Jak wiele oznaczeń z końca wojny, ten emblemat nigdy nie został oficjalnie zatwierdzony do reprezentowania 7. Grupy, ale mimo to umieszczano go na nosach ich myśliwców Me 163. Emblemat przedstawia Barona Münchhausena jadącego na butelkowej rakiecie, co jest dość trafnym motywem.
<Czech>: Emblém používaný 7. skupinou, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Stejně jako několik dalších pozdně válečných označení nebyl tento znak nikdy oficiálně schválen pro reprezentaci 7. skupiny, přesto byl umístěn na přídi jejich stíhaček Me 163. Znak zobrazuje barona Prášila jedoucího na raketě z láhve, což z něj činí docela vhodný motiv.
<Turkish>: Jagdgeschwader (Avcı Kanadı) 400, 7. Grup tarafından kullanılan bir amblem. Birçok savaş sonu amblemi gibi bu amblem de 7. Grubu temsil etmek üzere hiçbir zaman resmi olarak onaylanmamış, ancak yine de Me 163 avcı uçaklarının burnuna yerleştirilmiştir. Amblemde Baron Münchhausen bir şişe roketine binerken resmedilmiştir ve bu da onu oldukça uygun bir motif haline getirmektedir.
<Chinese>: 德\t国\t空\t军\t第 400 战\t斗\t机\t联\t队\t第 7 中\t队\t徽\t标。\t与\t战\t争\t末\t期\t设\t计\t的\t多\t数\t部\t队\t标\t识\t一\t样，\t该\t徽\t标\t从\t未\t获\t得\t官\t方\t正\t式\t采\t纳，\t不\t过\t第 7 中\t队\t的 Me 163 战\t斗\t机\t依\t旧\t在\t机\t鼻\t部\t位\t涂\t有\t该\t徽\t标。\t该\t标\t识\t主\t体\t为\t骑\t着\t酒\t瓶\t作\t为\t火\t箭\t的\t闵\t希\t豪\t森\t男\t爵，\t对\t于\t一\t支\t装\t备\t火\t箭\t战\t斗\t机\t的\t部\t队\t而\t言\t的\t确\t恰\t如\t其\t分。
<Japanese>: An emblem used by 7th Group, Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 400. Like several late-war markings this emblem was never officially approved to represent 7th group, but was nevertheless placed on the nose of their Me 163 fighters. The emblem depicts Baron Münchhausen riding a bottle rocket, making it quite an appropriate motif.

<English>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<French>: Un emblème de l'Escadron n° 11. Inspiré de l'insigne de l'escadron, ce marquage représente un couple d'aigles en tandem, en référence au premier avion utilisé par l'escadron - le Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus biplace - les aigles ont été choisis en particulier pour incarner un sens de la force et de la vitesse dans les airs. Ce marquage spécifique n'a été utilisé que plus récemment, sur la dérive des Typhoons en service au sein de l'escadron.
<Italian>: Un emblema della squadriglia n. 11. Ispirato al distintivo della squadriglia, questo stemma sullo scudo raffigura una coppia di aquile in tandem, un riferimento al primo aereo utilizzato dalla squadriglia - il Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus a due posti - le aquile sono state scelte in particolare per incarnare un senso di forza e velocità in l'aria. Questo contrassegno specifico è entrato in uso solo più recentemente, trovandosi sullo stabilizzatore verticale dei Typhoon in servizio con la squadriglia.
<German>: Ein Emblem des No. 11 Squadron. In Anlehnung an das Geschwaderabzeichen zeigt diese Schildmarkierung ein Adlerpaar in Tandem, eine Anspielung auf das erste Flugzeug der Staffel - die zweisitzige Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus - die Adler wurden insbesondere deshalb gewählt, um ein Gefühl von Stärke und Geschwindigkeit in der Luft zu verkörpern. Diese spezielle Markierung wird erst seit kürzerer Zeit in Gebrauch und findet sich auf dem Seitenleitwerk der Typhoons, die bei der Staffel im Einsatz sind.
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón No. 11. Inspirada en la insignia del escuadrón, esta marca de escudo representa un par de águilas en tándem, una referencia al primer avión operado por el escuadrón -el Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus biplaza - las águilas fueron elegidas en particular para encarnar una sensación de fuerza y velocidad en el aire. Esta marca específica se ha empezado a utilizar más recientemente, y se encuentra en el estabilizador vertical de los Typhoons en servicio con el escuadrón.
<Polish>: Emblemat 11 Dywizjonu. Zainspirowany odznaką dywizjonu, ten herb przedstawia parę orłów w tandemie, co odnosi się do pierwszego samolotu operowanego przez dywizjon - dwumiejscowego Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus. Orły zostały wybrane, aby ucieleśnić siłę i szybkość w powietrzu. Ten konkretny znak jest używany od stosunkowo niedawna, znajdując się na pionowym stateczniku Typhoonów w służbie dywizjonu.
<Czech>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Turkish>: No. 11 Filosu'nun bir amblemi. Filonun rozetinden esinlenen bu kalkan işareti, filo tarafından işletilen ilk uçak olan iki kişilik Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus'a bir gönderme olarak, ikili bir çift kartalı tasvir etmektedir; kartallar özellikle havadaki güç ve hız hissini somutlaştırmak için seçilmiştir. Bu özel işaret yakın zamanda kullanılmaya başlanmış olup, filoda hizmet veren Typhoon'ların dikey stabilizatörlerinde yer almaktadır.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 11 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t该\t盾\t徽\t取\t材\t自\t中\t队\t官\t方\t纹\t章\t图\t样，\t描\t绘\t了\t一\t对\t并\t列\t的\t雄\t鹰\t形\t象，\t象\t征\t着\t部\t队\t装\t备\t的\t首\t款\t战\t机 - 双\t座\t布\t局\t的\t维\t克\t斯 F.B 5\t“空\t中\t炮\t艇”\t战\t斗\t机；\t雄\t鹰\t则\t代\t表\t了\t空\t中\t速\t度\t与\t力\t量\t的\t王\t者，\t彰\t显\t出\t部\t队\t的\t军\t种\t特\t征。\t这\t一\t徽\t标\t最\t近\t才\t投\t入\t使\t用，\t见\t于\t中\t队\t下\t属\t“台\t风”\t战\t机\t的\t垂\t尾\t位\t置。
<Japanese>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Portuguese>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 11-ї ескадрильї. Натхненний значком ескадрильї, цей знак на щиті зображує пару орлів у тандемі, відсилання до першого літака ескадрильї — двомісного Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — орли були обрані, зокрема, щоб втілити відчуття сили та швидкості в повітрі. Це специфічне маркування почало використовуватися частіше, його можна знайти на вертикальному стабілізаторі Typhoon, що перебував на озброєнні ескадрильї.
<Serbian>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<Hungarian>: A 11. vadászrepülő-század emblémája, brit Királyi Légierő.
<Korean>: 제11비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 비행대의 배지에서 영감을 받은 이 엠블럼은 방패 문양에 한 쌍의 독수리가 나란히 서 있는 모습으로, 비행대가 최초로 운용한 항공기인 2인승 빅커스 F.B 5 건버스를 상징하고 있습니다. 특히, 공중에서의 힘과 속도감을 상징하기 위해 독수리를 채용하고 있었습니다. 이 표식은 최근에 사용되기 시작했으며, 비행대에서 운용 중인 타이푼의 수직 안정판에서 찾아볼 수 있습니다.
<Belarusian>: Emblem of the 11th Fighter Squadron, RAF
<Romanian>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’s badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<TChinese>: An emblem of No. 11 Squadron. Inspired by the squadron’\ts badge, this shield marking depicts a pair of eagles in tandem, a reference to the first aircraft operated by the squadron — the two seater Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus — eagles were chosen in particular to embody a sense of strength and speed in the air. This specific marking has only come into use more recently, being found on the vertical stabilizer of the Typhoons in service with the squadron.
<HChinese>: Emblem of the 11th Fighter Squadron, RAF
<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng của Sư đoàn số 11. Lấy cảm hứng từ huy hiệu của sư đoàn, biểu tượng hình chiếc khiên này miêu tả một cặp đại bàng song hành, một tượng trưng cho các máy bay đầu tiên được sư đoàn vận hành - máy bay hai chỗ Vickers F.B 5 Gunbus - đại bàng được chọn đặc biệt để tượng trưng cho sức mạnh và tốc độ trong không khí. Biểu tượng cụ thể này chỉ mới được sử dụng gần đây, được tìm thấy trên thân cân bằng dọc của các máy bay Typhoons đang phục vụ với sư đoàn.

<Vietnamese>: Huy hiệu tròn của Sư đoàn số 111

<English>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<French>: La cocarde de l'escadron n° 111. La plupart des cocardes d'escadron utilisent une barre en damier avec un emblème au centre, mais l'escadron 111 a opté pour quelque chose d'un peu plus frappant. Ce marquage particulier était apposé sur les McDonnell Douglas Phantoms exploités par l'escadron dans les années 1970. Comme la plupart des emblèmes de ce type, ils étaient placés sur le côté du nez, avec la pointe inférieure vers l'avant.
<Italian>: Coccarda della 111^ Squadriglia. La maggior parte delle coccarde delle squadriglie usavano una striscia a scacchi con lo stemma al cenetro, ma per quello della squadriglia 111 venne optato qualcosa di più appariscente. Questo particolare stemma era posto sui Phantom operanti negli anni 70. Era posto sul lato del muso, con il punto più basso rivolto verso davanti.
<German>: Kokarde des No. 111 Squadron. Die meisten Staffelkokarden hatten einen Balken mit Schachbrettmuster mit einem Abzeichen in der Mitte, aber in diesen Fall wählte No. 111 eine etwas markantere Darstellung. Diese besondere Markierung wurde auf den McDonnell Douglas Phantoms angebracht, die die Staffel in den 1970er nutzte. Wie die meisten Kokarden dieser Art waren sie an der Nasenseite angebracht, mit der unteren Spitze nach vorne.
<Spanish>: Escarapela del Escuadrón No. 111. La mayoría de las escarapelas de los escuadrones utilizaban una barra en forma de tablero de ajedrez con un emblema en el centro, aunque el No. 111, en este ejemplo, optó por algo un poco más llamativo. Esta marca en particular se colocó en los McDonnell Douglas Phantom operados por el escuadrón en la década de 1970. Como la mayoría de las escarapelas de este tipo, se colocaban a lo largo del morro, con la punta inferior hacia delante.
<Polish>: Kokarda 111 Dywizjonu. Większość kokard dywizjonowych miała szachownicowy pas z emblematem w centrum, jednak 111 Dywizjon w tym przykładzie wybrał coś bardziej uderzającego. To oznaczenie znajdowało się na samolotach McDonnell Douglas Phantom operowanych przez dywizjon w latach 70. Jak większość tego typu kokard, były umieszczone wzdłuż boku nosa, z dolnym punktem skierowanym do przodu.
<Czech>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<Turkish>: No. 111 Filosunun rozeti. Çoğu filo rozetinde ortasında bir amblem bulunan bir dama tahtası çubuğu kullanılırdı, ancak bu örnekte 111 No.lu Filo biraz daha çarpıcı bir şey tercih etmiştir. Bu özel işaret 1970'lerde filo tarafından işletilen McDonnell Douglas Phantom'ların üzerine yerleştirilmiştir. Bu tipteki çoğu yuvarlak işaret gibi, alt noktası öne gelecek şekilde burnun yan tarafı boyunca konumlandırılmıştı.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 111 飞\t行\t中\t队\t识\t别\t徽\t标。\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t识\t别\t条\t带\t大\t多\t采\t用\t棋\t盘\t格\t纹 + 部\t队\t徽\t标\t的\t组\t合，\t而\t第 111 飞\t行\t中\t队\t却\t不\t走\t寻\t常\t路\t采\t用\t了\t更\t具\t视\t觉\t冲\t击\t力\t的\t闪\t电\t图\t案。\t这\t一\t样\t式\t的\t识\t别\t条\t带\t主\t要\t见\t于\t上\t世\t纪 70 年\t代\t中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t麦\t克\t唐\t纳\t-\t道\t格\t拉\t斯\t“鬼\t怪”\t战\t斗\t机，\t与\t其\t他\t同\t类\t标\t识\t一\t样\t喷\t绘\t在\t机\t鼻\t侧\t面，\t闪\t电\t下\t端\t指\t向\t前\t方。
<Japanese>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<Portuguese>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<Ukrainian>: Рондель 111-ї ескадрильї. Більшість ескадрильних ронделів використовували шахову смугу з емблемою в центрі, хоча 111-а у цьому прикладі вибрала щось більш яскраве. Це маркування було розміщене на McDonnell Douglas Phantom, якими керувала ескадрилья в 1970-х роках. Як і більшість ронделів цього типу, вони розташовувалися збоку від носа нижньою точкою вперед.
<Serbian>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.
<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Légierő 111. repülőszázadának emblémája. Leuchars, Skócia.
<Korean>: 제111비행대의 라운델입니다. 대다수의 경우 비행대 엠블럼이 중앙에 위치하고, 양 옆으로 체크무늬가 존재했는데, 제111비행대의 경우 더 '독특한' 방향을 선택하였습니다. 이 마킹은 1970년대에 운용했던 맥도넬 더글러스 팬텀에 사용되었으며, 기수 측면에 부착되어 있었습니다.
<Belarusian>: Emblem of 111th Squadron flash, Leuchars, RAF
<Romanian>: The roundel of No. 111 Squadron. Most squadron roundels used a checkerboard bar with an emblem in the center, though No. 111 in this example opted for something a bit more striking. This particular marking was placed on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms operated by the squadron in the 1970s. Like most roundels of this type they were positioned along the side of the nose, with the lower point towards the front.

<HChinese>: Emblem of 111th Squadron flash, Leuchars, RAF
<Vietnamese>: Huy hiệu tròn của Sư đoàn số 111. Hầu hết các huy hiệu của các sư đoàn sử dụng một thanh ô vuông kèm theo một biểu tượng ở giữa, tuy nhiên, Sư đoàn số 111 trong ví dụ này đã chọn một điều gì đó nổi bật hơn. Biểu tượng cụ thể này được đặt trên các máy bay McDonnell Douglas Phantoms được sư đoàn vận hành trong những năm 1970. Giống như hầu hết các huy hiệu tròn của loại này, chúng được đặt dọc theo bên của mũi máy bay, với điểm thấp nhất hướng về phía trước.

<Korean>: 영국 왕립공군 제43비행대(No. 43 Squadron RAF)의 "싸우는 수탉" 엠블럼 (후기형)
<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng "Fighting Cock" (bản mới), Sư đoàn số 43

<English>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<French>: Un emblème de l'escadron n° 43. Cet emblème représente un coq de bruyère et a été utilisé au début des années 1970. Le marquage est dérivé de l'insigne de l'escadron qui représente également un coq coloré. Les pilotes de cet escadron ont également utilisé ces oiseaux pour décorer leurs avions pendant la Seconde Guerre mondiale, avec plusieurs variantes connues. Ce marquage particulier se trouvait exclusivement sur les McDonnell Douglas Phantom en service au sein de la 43e escadrille, et était placé sur la dérive.
<Italian>: Lo stemma della squadriglia N° 43. Rappresenta un gallo da combattimento che venne utilizzato nei primi anni 70. Lo stemma derivava dalla toppa della squadriglia che raffigurava un galletto variopinto; i piloti di questa squadriglia usavano questi uccelli per adornare i loro aerei nella Seconda Guerra Mondiale con diverse variazioni. Questo stemma in particolare venne raffigurato esclusivamente sui McDonnell Douglas Phantom in servizio con la 43^ e posizionato sullo stabilizzatore verticale.
<German>: Ein Abzeichen des No. 43 Squadron. Dieses Abzeichen zeigt einen Wildhahn und wurde Anfang der 1970er Jahre eingeführt. Das Abzeichen ist vom Abzeichen der Staffel abgeleitet, das ebenfalls einen bunten Hahn zeigt; die Piloten dieser Staffel schmückten ihre Flugzeuge auch im Zweiten Weltkrieg mit diesen Vögeln, wobei mehrere Varianten bekannt sind. Diese besondere Abzeichen befand sich ausschließlich auf der McDonnell Douglas Phantom, die bei der No. 43 im Einsatz war, und war auf dem Seitenleitwerk angebracht.
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón No. 43. Esta marca muestra un gallo de pelea, y empezó a utilizarse a principios de la década de 1970. La marca deriva de la insignia del escuadrón, que también representa un colorido gallo; los pilotos de este escuadrón también utilizaron estas aves para adornar sus aviones en la Segunda Guerra Mundial, con varias variaciones conocidas. Esta marca en particular se encontraba exclusivamente en los McDonnell Douglas Phantom en servicio con el No. 43, y estaba colocada en el estabilizador vertical.
<Polish>: Emblemat Eskadry nr 43. Ten znak przedstawia bojowego koguta i zaczął być używany na początku lat 70. XX wieku. Emblemat wywodzi się z herbu eskadry, który również przedstawia kolorowego koguta; piloci tej eskadry używali tych ptaków do ozdabiania swoich samolotów podczas II wojny światowej, z kilkoma znanymi wariantami. Ten konkretny emblemat znajdował się wyłącznie na samolotach McDonnell Douglas Phantom w służbie Eskadry nr 43 i był umieszczony na pionowym stabilizatorze.
<Czech>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<Turkish>: No. 43 Filosunun bir amblemi. Bu amblem bir gamecock kuşunu göstermektedir ve 1970'lerin başında kullanılmaya başlanmıştır. Bu işaret filonun renkli bir horozu da tasvir eden rozetinden türetilmiştir; bu filonun pilotları İkinci Dünya Savaşında da uçaklarını süslemek için bu kuşları kullanmışlardır ve bilinen çeşitli varyasyonları vardır. Bu özel işaret sadece No. 43'te hizmet veren McDonnell Douglas Phantom'larda bulunurdu ve dikey stabilizatör üzerinde konumlandırılmıştı.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 43 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t该\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t图\t案\t为\t源\t自\t部\t队\t纹\t章\t图\t样\t的\t斗\t鸡\t形\t象，\t于\t上\t世\t纪 70 年\t代\t初\t期\t投\t入\t使\t用。\t早\t在\t第\t二\t次\t世\t界\t大\t战\t期\t间，\t来\t自\t第 43 中\t队\t的\t飞\t行\t员\t们\t就\t用\t斗\t鸡\t图\t案\t装\t饰\t自\t己\t的\t战\t机。\t这\t一\t样\t式\t的\t徽\t标\t仅\t见\t于\t中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t麦\t克\t唐\t纳\t-\t道\t格\t拉\t斯\t“鬼\t怪”\t战\t斗\t机，\t位\t于\t垂\t尾\t部\t位。
<Japanese>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<Portuguese>: An emblem of No. 43 Squadron. This marking displays a gamecock, and came into use during the early 1970s. The marking is derived from the badge of the squadron which also depicts a colorful rooster; pilots of this squadron also used these birds to adorn their aircraft in the Second World War, with several known variations. This particular marking was found exclusively on the McDonnell Douglas Phantoms in service with No. 43, and was positioned on the vertical stabilizer.
<Ukrainian>: Емблема 43-ї ескадрильї. Це маркування відображає півня і ввійшло в ужиток на початку 1970-х років. Маркування походить від значка ескадрильї, на якому також зображений різнокольоровий півень; Пілоти цієї ескадрильї також використовували цих птахів для прикраси своїх літаків під час Другої світової війни, з кількома відомими варіантами. Це маркування було знайдено виключно на McDonnell Douglas Phantom, які були на озброєнні у 43-ї, і було розташоване на вертикальному стабілізаторі.

<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Légierő 43. századának emblémája, Royal Air Force Leuchars (1978).
<Korean>: 제43비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 투계가 표시된 이 마킹은 1970년대 초부터 사용되기 시작했습니다. 이 마킹은 화려한 모습의 수탉이 그려진 비행대의 배지에서 유래한 것으로, 이 비행대의 조종사들은 2차 세계대전 당시에도 수탉을 그려 항공기를 장식했으며, 여러 가지 파생형이 존재했습니다. 이 표식은 제43비행대 소속 맥도넬 더글러스 팬텀에 사용되었으며 수직 안정판에 위치해 있었습니다.

<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng của Sư đoàn số 43. Hình này hiển thị một con gà đá, và được sử dụng từ đầu những năm 1970. Biểu tượng này được lấy cảm hứng từ huy hiệu của sư đoàn mà cũng miêu tả một con gà trống sặc sỡ; các phi công của sư đoàn này cũng đã sử dụng những con gà này để trang trí máy bay của họ trong Thế chiến thứ hai, với một số biến thể được biết đến. Biểu tượng cụ thể này chỉ được tìm thấy trên các máy bay McDonnell Douglas Phantom được phục vụ trong Sư đoàn số 43, và được đặt trên thân cân bằng dọc.

<English>: A marking of Staff Group, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 77. The emblem depicts an outstretched skeletal hand, used on the Ju 88 aircraft of the group. The hand was painted on the side of the nose under the cockpit, as if to grasp the side window.
<French>: Un marquage du Staff Group, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 77. L'emblème représente une main squelettique tendue, utilisé sur les avions Ju 88 du groupe. La main était peinte sur le côté sous le cockpit, comme s'elle saisissait le côté de la fenêtre.
<Italian>: Uno stemma del gruppo, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Stormo Bombardieri di Picchiata) 77. Lo stemma ritrae una mano scheletrica, usato sugli aerei Ju 88 operanti nel gruppo. La mano era dipinta sul lato del muso sotto la cabina di pilotaggio, come se volesse agguantare il finestrino.
<German>: Ein Kennzeichen der Stabsgruppe des Sturzkampfgeschwaders 77. Das Abzeichen stellt eine ausgestreckte Skeletthand dar, die auf den Ju 88-Flugzeugen der Gruppe verwendet wurde. Die Hand wurde auf die Seite der Nase unter dem Cockpit gemalt, als ob sie das Seitenfenster greifen wollte.
<Spanish>: Una marca del Grupo de Mando, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Ala de Bombarderos en Inmersión) 77. El emblema representa una mano esquelética extendida, utilizada en los aviones Ju 88 del grupo. La mano estaba pintada en el lateral del morro, bajo la cabina, como si quisiera agarrarse a la ventanilla lateral.
<Polish>: Oznaczenie Grupy Sztabowej, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Skrzydło Bombowców Nurkujących) 77. Emblemat przedstawia wyciągniętą szkieletową dłoń, używany na samolotach Ju 88 grupy. Dłoń była malowana na boku nosa pod kabiną, jakby chwytała boczne okno.
<Czech>: Označení Staff Group, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dive Bomber Wing) 77. Znak znázorňuje nataženou kostlivou ruku, používanou na letounech Ju 88 této skupiny. Ruka byla namalována na boku přídě pod kokpitem, jako by se chytala bočního okénka.
<Turkish>: Kurmay Grubu, Sturzkampfgeschwader (Dalış Bombardıman Kanadı) 77'ye ait bir işaret. Amblem, grubun Ju 88 uçaklarında kullanılan uzanmış bir iskelet elini tasvir etmektedir. El, kokpitin altındaki burnun yan tarafına, sanki yan pencereyi kavrayacakmış gibi boyanmıştır.

<English>: Another milestone in the history of War Thunder has been reached - 121,784 players that were online at the same time! May these memorable decal stop you forgetting about that achievement.

Un'altra pietra miliare nella storia di war Thunder è stata raggiunta - 121.784 giocatori online contemporaneamente!
Possano queste indimenticabili immagini non farti mai dimenticare questo traguardo.

<English>: The emblem of the 269th Mechanized Infantry Brigade, ROC. Formed under the 6th Army Corps, the brigade operates various vehicles, including the CM-11 and CM-22 M113. Like many similar emblems they were rarely if ever directly applied to combat vehicles, only sporadically under limited conditions such as ceremonies or displays. The emblem depicts a roaring lion on a tricolor background, mirroring the yellow, blue and red scheme of the armored brigades it shares close ties with.
<French>: L'emblème de la 269e Brigade d'infanterie mécanisée de la République de Chine. Formée sous l'égide du 6e Corps d'armée, la brigade utilise de nombreux véhicules tels que le CM11 et le CM22. Comme de nombreux emblèmes de ce genre, ils n'étaient que rarement voire jamais directement utilisés sur les véhicules et seulement sporadiquement dans des conditions spéciales comme pour des cérémonies ou des démonstrations. L'emblème représente un lion rugissant sur fond tricolore, reflétant les couleurs jaune, bleu et rouge des brigades blindées avec lesquelles elle partage des liens étroits.
<Italian>: Stemma della 269^ Brigata di fanteria meccanizzata, ROC. Formata sotto il 6° Corpo d'Armata, la brigata gestisce vari veicoli, tra cui il CM-11 e il CM-22 M113. Come molti emblemi simili, venivano raramente, se non mai, applicati direttamente ai veicoli da combattimento, solo sporadicamente in condizioni limitate come cerimonie o esibizioni. Lo stemma raffigura un leone ruggente su sfondo tricolore, rispecchiando lo schema giallo, blu e rosso delle brigate corazzate con cui condivide stretti legami.
<Spanish>: Emblema de la 269ª Brigada de Infantería Mecanizada, ROC. Formada bajo el 6º Cuerpo de Ejército, la brigada opera varios vehículos, entre ellos los M113 CM-11 y CM-22. Como muchos emblemas similares, rara vez o nunca se aplicaron directamente a vehículos de combate, sólo esporádicamente en condiciones limitadas, como ceremonias o exhibiciones. El emblema representa un león rugiente sobre un fondo tricolor, que refleja el esquema amarillo, azul y rojo de las brigadas blindadas con las que comparte estrechos vínculos.
<Russian>: Эмблема 269-й механизированной пехотной бригады армии Китая. Сформированная в рамках 6-го армейского корпуса, бригада эксплуатирует различные транспортные средства, в том числе CM-11 и CM-22 M113. Как и многие другие подобные эмблемы, они редко, если вообще когда-либо наносились непосредственно на боевые машины, лишь эпизодически, в ограниченных случаях, таких как церемонии или демонстрации. На эмблеме изображён рычащий лев на трёхцветном фоне, что отражает жёлто-сине-красную схему бронетанковых бригад, с которыми она тесно связана.
<Polish>: Emblemat 269. Zmechanizowanej Brygady Piechoty, Republika Chińska (ROC). Brygada została utworzona w ramach 6. Korpusu Armijnego i operuje różnymi pojazdami, w tym CM-11 i CM-22 M113. Podobnie jak wiele innych emblematów, rzadko umieszczano go bezpośrednio na pojazdach bojowych – jeśli w ogóle – a jedynie sporadycznie w ograniczonych sytuacjach, takich jak ceremonie czy pokazy. Emblemat przedstawia ryczącego lwa na tle w trzech kolorach, odpowiadających żółtemu, niebieskiemu i czerwonemu schematowi brygad pancernych, z którymi jednostka jest blisko związana.
<Czech>: Emblém 269. mechanizované pěší brigády ČLR. Brigáda je zformována v rámci 6. armádního sboru a provozuje různá vozidla, včetně CM-11 a CM-22 M113. Stejně jako mnoho podobných emblémů byly zřídkakdy, pokud vůbec, použity přímo na bojových vozidlech, pouze sporadicky v omezených podmínkách, jako jsou ceremoniály nebo přehlídky. Znak zobrazuje řvoucího lva na tříbarevném pozadí, což odráží žluté, modré a červené schéma obrněných brigád, s nimiž má úzké vazby.
<Turkish>: Çin Cumhuriyeti 269. Mekanize Piyade Tugayı'nın amblemi. 6. Kolordu'ya bağlı olarak kurulan tugay CM-11 ve CM-22 M113 dahil olmak üzere çeşitli araçlar kullanmaktadır. Benzer pek çok amblem gibi bu amblemler de nadiren doğrudan savaş araçlarına uygulanmış, sadece törenler veya gösteriler gibi sınırlı koşullar altında ara sıra kullanılmıştır. Amblem üç renkli bir arka plan üzerinde kükreyen bir aslanı tasvir eder ve yakın bağları olan zırhlı tugayların sarı, mavi ve kırmızı düzenini yansıtır.
<Chinese>: 中\t华\t民\t国\t陆\t军\t第 269 机\t械\t化\t步\t兵\t旅\t徽\t标。\t该\t旅\t隶\t属\t第 6 军\t团，\t装\t备\t有 CM-11\t“勇\t虎”\t主\t战\t坦\t克、\tCM-22 自\t行\t迫\t击\t炮\t等\t装\t甲\t车\t辆。\t与\t多\t数\t部\t队\t徽\t章\t相\t仿，\t该\t标\t识\t极\t少\t直\t接\t涂\t装\t于\t战\t斗\t车\t辆，\t仅\t偶\t见\t于\t阅\t兵\t或\t装\t备\t展\t出\t等\t特\t定\t场\t合。\t徽\t章\t主\t体\t为\t三\t色\t背\t景\t上\t的\t怒\t吼\t雄\t狮，\t延\t续\t了\t装\t甲\t旅\t惯\t用\t的\t黄、\t蓝、\t红\t三\t色\t基\t调，\t强\t调\t部\t队\t机\t械\t化\t步\t兵\t的\t属\t性。

<TChinese>: 中\t華\t民\t國\t陸\t軍\t第 269 機\t械\t步\t兵\t旅\t“雄\t獅”\t徽\t標
<HChinese>: "Lion" emblem of the 269th Mechanized Infantry Brigade, ROCA
<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng của Lữ đoàn bộ binh cơ giới 269, ROC. Được thành lập trực thuộc Quân đoàn 6, lữ đoàn vận hành nhiều loại xe khác nhau, bao gồm CM-11 và CM-22 M113. Giống như nhiều biểu tượng tương tự, chúng hiếm khi được áp dụng trực tiếp cho các phương tiện chiến đấu, chỉ thỉnh thoảng trong những điều kiện hạn chế như nghi lễ hoặc trưng bày. Biểu tượng mô tả một con sư tử gầm trên nền ba màu, phản chiếu sơ đồ màu vàng, xanh lam và đỏ của các lữ đoàn thiết giáp mà nó có mối quan hệ chặt chẽ.

<French>: Pin-up "Oomph Gal", 408e Escadron de la RCAF
<Chinese>: 加\t拿\t大\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 408 飞\t行\t中\t队\t“热\t情\t姑\t娘”\t涂\t鸦
<Korean>: "Oomph Gal" 핀업, 왕립 캐나다 공군 제 408 비행대
<Vietnamese>: Hình pin-up 'Oomph Gal', của Sư đoàn số 408 của Không quân Hoàng gia Canada

<English>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<French>: La pin-up " Oomph Gal " du Lancaster KB929 en 1945, 408e escadron de la RCAF. Comme beaucoup de pin-up de l'époque, celle-ci est inspirée d'une actrice populaire de l'époque, Ann Sheridan, que les médias appelaient la "Oomph girl" - bien qu'elle-même ne soit pas tout à fait sûre de la signification du titre de "Oomph girl". La pin-up a été peinte juste sous le côté du cockpit.
<Italian>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<German>: Das "Oomph Gal" Pinup der Lancaster KB929 von 1945, No 408 Squadron, RCAF. Wie viele Pinups dieser Ära, basierte es auf einer populären Schauspielerin dieser Zeit, Ann Sheridan, welche von den Medien als "Oomph girl" betitelt wurde - wobei jedoch berichtet wurde, das sie selber gar nicht sicher war, was der Titel "Oomph girl" tatsächlich bedeuten sollte. Das Pinup wurde direkt unter der Seite des Cockpits aufgebracht.
<Spanish>: Pin-up "Oomph Gal" del Lancaster KB929 durante 1945, Escuadrón No. 408 de la RCAF. Como muchos pin-ups de la época, este ejemplo se basaba en una popular actriz de la época, Ann Sheridan, a la que los medios de comunicación llamaban la "Chica Oomph" - aunque se decía que ella misma no estaba del todo segura de lo que significaba realmente el título de "Chica Oomph". El pin-up se pintó justo debajo del lateral de la cabina.
<Polish>: „Oomph Gal” pin-up Lancastra KB929 w 1945 roku, 408 Dywizjon RCAF. Jak wiele pin-upów z tamtej epoki, ten przykład był oparty na popularnej wówczas aktorce, Ann Sheridan, która była nazywana przez media „Oomph girl” - chociaż sama aktorka nie była całkowicie pewna, co właściwie oznaczał ten tytuł. Pin-up został namalowany tuż pod bokiem kabiny.
<Czech>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Turkish>: Lancaster KB929'un 1945 yılındaki “Oomph Gal” pin-up'ı, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Dönemin pek çok pin-up'ı gibi bu örnek de medya tarafından “Oomph kızı” olarak lanse edilen dönemin popüler aktrisi Ann Sheridan'a dayanmaktadır - ancak kendisi de “Oomph kızı” unvanının gerçekte ne anlama geldiğinden tam olarak emin olmadığını belirtmiştir. Resim kokpitin yan tarafının hemen altına boyanmıştır.
<Chinese>: 该\t涂\t鸦\t见\t于 1945 年\t间\t隶\t属\t于\t加\t拿\t大\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 408 轰\t炸\t机\t中\t队\t的 1 架\t兰\t开\t斯\t特\t轰\t炸\t机 (编\t号 KB929) 座\t舱\t玻\t璃\t侧\t面。\t同\t一\t时\t期\t的\t机\t鼻\t涂\t鸦\t往\t往\t以\t当\t时\t走\t红\t的\t女\t演\t员\t形\t象\t作\t为\t创\t作\t原\t型，\t这\t一\t图\t案\t也\t来\t自\t大\t众\t媒\t体\t所\t评\t选\t的\t“热\t情\t姑\t娘”\t安·谢\t里\t登；\t尽\t管\t即\t使\t是\t演\t员\t自\t己\t可\t能\t也\t对\t标\t语\t所\t含\t的\t意\t味\t不\t甚\t明\t了。
<Japanese>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Portuguese>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Ukrainian>: Пінап «Oomph Gal» на Lancaster KB929 у 1945 році, 408-а ескадрилья RCAF. Як і багато пінапів тієї епохи, цей приклад базувався на популярній на той час актрисі Енн Шерідан, яку в медіа називали «дівчиною Oomph», хоча вона сама не зовсім впевнена, що титул «дівчина Oomph» насправді означав. Пінап був намальований прямо під бортиком кабіни.
<Serbian>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Hungarian>: Oomph Gal pin-up. Kanadai Királyi Légierő 408. százada (1945).
<Korean>: 캐나다 공군의 랭카스터 KB929에 부착된 "움프 걸" 핀업입니다. 다른 핀업들처럼 당대 유명한 여배우였던 앤 셰리든의 모습을 따라 제작되었습니다. 앤 셰리든은 미디어에서 "움프 걸"로 불렸지만, 그녀 자신도 "움프 걸" 이라는 칭호가 실제로는 어떤 의미인지는 잘 알지 못했다고 합니다. 이 핀업은 조종석 측면 바로 아래에 그려져 있었습니다.
<Romanian>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<TChinese>: The "Oomph Gal" pin-up of Lancaster KB929 during 1945, No. 408 Squadron RCAF. Like many pin-ups of the era this example was based on a popular actress at the time, Ann Sheridan, who was pinned as the "Oomph girl" by the media — though she herself was noted to not be entirely sure what the title of "Oomph girl" actually meant. The pin-up was painted just under the side of the cockpit.
<Vietnamese>: Bức họa 'Oomph Gal' trên máy bay Lancaster KB929 trong năm 1945, của Sư đoàn số 408 của Không quân Hoàng gia Canada. Giống như nhiều hình pin-up của thời đại đó, ví dụ này được dựa trên một nữ diễn viên nổi tiếng vào thời điểm đó, Ann Sheridan, người được truyền thông gắn với danh hiệu 'Oomph girl' - mặc dù cô ấy chính bản thân cũng không chắc chắn rằng "Oomph girl" có ý nghĩa gì. Bức họa pin-up này được vẽ ngay dưới bên hông buồng lái.

<English>: The personal marking of (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. David’s marking links directly to his name, with Scottie being a common affectionate nickname of Scott. Incidentally this is also the nickname of the Scottish Terrier dog breed, which also makes an appearance in David’s roundel. The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.
<French>: Le marquage personnel de (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, Escadron No. 603, RAuxAF. Le marquage de David est directement lié à son nom, Scottie étant un surnom affectueux courant de Scott. Il s'agit également du surnom de la race de chien Scottish Terrier, qui apparaît également dans la cocarde de David. Le marquage et l'inscription qui l'accompagne ont été placés sous l'arrière de l'échappement du moteur de son Spitfire en 1941.
<Italian>: The personal marking of (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. David’s marking links directly to his name, with Scottie being a common affectionate nickname of Scott. Incidentally this is also the nickname of the Scottish Terrier dog breed, which also makes an appearance in David’s roundel. The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.
<German>: Das persönliche Abzeichen von (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. Davids Markierung ist direkt mit seinem Namen verbunden, mit Scottie ein häufiger Spitzname von Scott. Zufälligerweise ist dies auch der Spitzname der Schottisch-Terrier Hunderasse, welche auch in Davids Kokarde auftaucht. Das Abzeichen und die dazugehörige Inschrift waren 1941 unter dem Ende der Auspuffrohre seiner Spitfire angebracht.
<Spanish>: El distintivo personal de (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, Escuadrón No. 603, RAuxAF. El distintivo de David está directamente relacionado con su nombre, ya que Scottie es un apodo cariñoso común de Scott. Por cierto, también es el apodo de la raza de perro Scottish Terrier, que también aparece en la escarapela de David. La marca y la inscripción que la acompaña se colocaron debajo de la parte trasera del tubo de escape del motor de su Spitfire en 1941.
<Russian>: Персональная эмблема "Scottie", пилот Фрэнсис "Скотти" Скотт-Молден, 603-я эскадрилья RAF, 1941
<Polish>: Osobisty emblemat (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, 603 Dywizjon, RAuxAF. Emblemat Davida odnosi się bezpośrednio do jego nazwiska, ponieważ "Scottie" to popularne pieszczotliwe przezwisko od Scott. Przypadkowo jest to również nazwa rasy psa - Scottish Terrier, który pojawia się w emblemacie Davida. Oznaczenie wraz z napisem było umieszczone pod tyłem wylotu silnika na jego Spitfire w 1941 roku.
<Czech>: The personal marking of (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF. David’s marking links directly to his name, with Scottie being a common affectionate nickname of Scott. Incidentally this is also the nickname of the Scottish Terrier dog breed, which also makes an appearance in David’s roundel. The marking and accompanying inscription was positioned under the back of the engine exhaust on his Spitfire in 1941.
<Turkish>: (Francis) David Stephen Scott-Malden, No. 603 Squadron, RAuxAF'ın kişisel işaretlemesi. David'in işaretlemesi doğrudan ismiyle bağlantılıdır; Scottie, Scott'un yaygın bir sevgi dolu takma adıdır. Tesadüfen bu aynı zamanda İskoç Terrier köpek cinsinin de lakabıdır ve David'in rozetinde de yer almaktadır. İşaret ve beraberindeki yazı 1941 yılında Spitfire'ının motor egzozunun arka kısmının altına yerleştirilmiştir.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t辅\t助\t空\t军\t第 603 飞\t行\t中\t队\t佛\t朗\t西\t斯·戴\t维·斯\t蒂\t芬·斯\t科\t特\t-\t马\t尔\t登\t个\t人\t涂\t鸦。\t戴\t维\t的\t个\t人\t涂\t鸦\t与\t他\t的\t姓\t氏\t相\t关：\t“斯\t科\t蒂”\t在\t当\t时\t是\t斯\t科\t特\t的\t常\t见\t亲\t密\t昵\t称，\t而\t这\t一\t称\t呼\t恰\t巧\t也\t是\t苏\t格\t兰\t梗\t犬\t的\t外\t号\t之\t一；\t戴\t维\t的\t个\t人\t涂\t鸦\t乃\t至\t识\t别\t条\t带\t也\t因\t此\t选\t取\t了\t苏\t格\t兰\t梗\t的\t形\t象。\t戴\t维·马\t尔\t登\t喷\t火\t座\t机 1941 年\t时\t在\t引\t擎\t排\t气\t管\t后\t方\t绘\t有\t这\t一\t涂\t鸦\t与\t对\t应\t的\t标\t语。

Позначка Девіда безпосередньо пов’язана з його ім’ям, а Скотті – це загальне ласкаве прізвисько Скотта. <English>: An emblem used by Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. The group operated numerous aircraft, with the emblem being specific to the particular aircraft it was placed on. The emblem came in several colorations depending on the group, this blue marking of Fliegende Staffel (Flying Group) 2 was placed on the tail of the F-104 Starfighters they operated.
<French>: Un emblème utilisé par le Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. Le groupe a opéré sur nombreux avions, avec l'emblème étant spécifique à l'avion particulier sur lequel il a été placé. L'emblème est venu dans plusieurs colorations dépendant du groupe, ce marquage bleu du Fliegende Staffel (Flying Group) 2 était placé sur la queue des F-104 Starfighters qu'ils opéraient.
<Italian>: An emblem used by Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. The group operated numerous aircraft, with the emblem being specific to the particular aircraft it was placed on. The emblem came in several colorations depending on the group, this blue marking of Fliegende Staffel (Flying Group) 2 was placed on the tail of the F-104 Starfighters they operated.
<German>: Ein Abzeichen, das vom Jagdbombergeschwader 33 verwendet wurde. Die Gruppe betrieb zahlreiche Flugzeuge, wobei das Abzeichen dem jeweiligen Flugzeug zugeordnet war. Das Abzeichen gab es je nach Gruppe in verschiedenen Farben. Dieses blaue Abzeichen der Fliegenden Staffel 2 befand sich auf dem Heck der von ihr eingesetzten F-104 Starfighter.
<Spanish>: Emblema utilizado por la Jagdbombergeschwader (Ala de Cazabombarderos) 33. El grupo operaba numerosos aviones, y el emblema era específico del avión concreto en el que se colocaba. El emblema tenía varias coloraciones según el grupo, esta marca azul del Fliegende Staffel (Grupo Volante) 2 se colocaba en la cola de los F-104 Starfighters que operaban.
<Polish>: Emblemat używany przez Jagdbombergeschwader 33. Grupa operowała licznymi samolotami, a emblemat był specyficzny dla konkretnego samolotu, na którym był umieszczony. Emblemat występował w kilku kolorach w zależności od grupy, ten niebieski znak Fliegende Staffel 2 był umieszczony na ogonie samolotów F-104 Starfighter, które operowali.
<Czech>: Emblém používaný Jagdbombergeschwader (Fighter-Bomber Wing) 33. Skupina provozovala řadu letounů, přičemž znak byl specifický pro konkrétní letoun, na kterém byl umístěn. Emblém existoval v několika barevných provedeních v závislosti na skupině, toto modré označení Fliegende Staffel (Létající skupiny) 2 bylo umístěno na ocase jimi provozovaných stíhaček F-104 Starfighter.
<Turkish>: Jagdbombergeschwader (Avcı-Bombardıman Kanadı) 33 tarafından kullanılan bir amblem. Grup çok sayıda uçak kullanıyordu ve amblem, üzerine yerleştirildiği uçağa özeldi. Amblemin gruba bağlı olarak çeşitli renkleri vardı, Fliegende Staffel (Uçan Grup) 2'nin bu mavi işareti, kullandıkları F-104 Starfighter'ların kuyruğuna yerleştirilmişti.

<French>: Emblème de Tête de Renard, Escadron No. 12
<Spanish>: Emblema Cabeza de Zorro, Escuadrón No. 12
<Chinese>: 第 12 飞\t行\t中\t队\t“狐\t狸\t头”\t徽\t标
<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng đầu cáo, Phi đoàn số 12

<English>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<French>: Un emblème de l'escadron n° 12. L'emblème représente une tête de renard hargneuse, une reproduction fidèle de l'insigne de l'escadron. La tête de renard a été choisie comme emblème de la 12e escadrille car, en 1926, elle a été la première à être équipée du Fairey Fox, un chasseur puissant pour l'époque et un symbole fort de fierté pour le groupe. Ce marquage plus moderne a cependant été apposé sur plusieurs Buccaneer de la 12e escadrille, sur le côté des entrées d'air des moteurs.
<Italian>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<German>: Ein Emblem des No. 12 Squadron. Das Emblem zeigt einen knurrenden Fuchskopf, eine 1-zu-1 Abbildung vom Staffelabzeichen. Der Fuchskopf wurde als das Abzeichen für No. 12 gewählt, als 1926 die Staffel als Erste mit der Fairey Fox ausgestattet wurde, ein leistungsfähiger Jäger für seine Zeit und ein starkes Symbol von Stolz für die Gruppe. Dieses etwas modernisierte Abzeichen wurde jedoch auf einige Buccaneers Angriffsflugzeuge der No. 12 angebracht, und wurde auf die Seite der Triebswerkseinlässe platziert.
<Spanish>: Emblema del Escuadrón No. 12. El emblema representa una cabeza de zorro gruñendo, una reproducción idéntica de la insignia del escuadrón. Se eligió la cabeza de zorro como emblema del No. 12 porque en 1926 fue el primer escuadrón equipado con el Fairey Fox, un poderoso caza para la época y un fuerte símbolo de orgullo para el grupo. Sin embargo, esta marca más moderna se colocó en varios atacantes Buccaneer del No. 12, y se situó en el lateral de las tomas de los motores.
<Polish>: Emblemat Eskadry nr 12. Emblemat przedstawia głowę warczącego lisa, wierną kopię herbu eskadry. Głowa lisa została wybrana jako emblemat Eskadry nr 12, ponieważ w 1926 roku była to pierwsza eskadra wyposażona w samolot Fairey Fox, potężny myśliwiec tamtych czasów i silny symbol dumy dla grupy. Ten bardziej nowoczesny emblemat został jednak umieszczony na kilku atakujących samolotach Buccaneer Eskadry nr 12 i znajdował się po bokach wlotów silników.
<Czech>: An emblem of No. 12 Squadron. The emblem depicts a snarling fox head, a one-to-one rendition of the squadron badge. The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.
<Turkish>: No. 12 Filosunun amblemi. Amblem, filo rozetinin bire bir yorumu olan hırlayan bir tilki kafasını tasvir etmektedir. Tilki kafası 12. Filo için amblem olarak seçilmiştir çünkü 1926 yılında, o dönem için güçlü bir avcı uçağı ve grup için güçlü bir gurur sembolü olan Fairey Fox ile donatılan ilk filo olmuşlardır. Ancak bu daha modern amblem 12. Filo'nun birçok Buccaneer hücum uçağına yerleştirilmiş ve motor girişlerinin yan tarafına yerleştirilmiştir.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 12 飞\t行\t中\t队\t徽\t标。\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t忠\t实\t还\t原\t了\t官\t方\t纹\t章\t中\t咆\t哮\t的\t狐\t狸\t头\t图\t案。\t中\t队\t于 1926 年\t成\t为\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t中\t首\t支\t换\t装\t费\t尔\t雷\t“狐”\t式\t战\t斗\t机\t的\t部\t队；\t为\t了\t彰\t显\t率\t先\t换\t装\t新\t型\t战\t机\t的\t自\t豪\t之\t情，\t中\t队\t决\t定\t将\t狐\t狸\t形\t象\t列\t入\t官\t方\t纹\t章，\t确\t立\t为\t部\t队\t的\t象\t征。\t游\t戏\t中\t的\t这\t枚\t贴\t花\t则\t是\t后\t期\t以\t现\t代\t风\t格\t重\t绘\t的\t版\t本，\t主\t要\t见\t于\t第 12 中\t队\t装\t备\t的\t掠\t夺\t者\t攻\t击\t机，\t喷\t绘\t于\t引\t擎\t进\t气\t道\t两\t侧。

The fox head was chosen as the emblem for No. 12 as during 1926 they were the first squadron to be equipped with the Fairey Fox, a powerful fighter for the time and a strong symbol of pride for the group. This more modern marking however was placed on several Buccaneer attackers of No. 12, and was positioned on the side of the engine intakes.

<Ukrainian>: Емблема 12-ї ескадрильї. На емблемі зображена голова лиса, що гарчить, один в один із виконанням значка ескадрильї. Голову лиса було обрано як емблему для 12-ї, оскільки в 1926 році вони були першою ескадрильєю, яка була оснащена Fairey Fox, потужним винищувачем того часу та сильним символом гордості для групи. Однак це більш сучасне маркування було розміщено на кількох штурмовиках Buccaneer 12-ї і було розташоване збоку від впускних отворів двигуна.

<Hungarian>: A brit Királyi Légierő Lossiemouth Buccaneer ezrede 12. századának emblémája.
<Korean>: 제12비행대의 엠블럼입니다. 이 엠블럼은 비행대 배지를 표현한 으르렁거리는 모습의 여우가 그려져 있습니다. 여우의 머리는 1926년 당시 강력한 성능의 전투기였던 페어리 폭스를 최초로 운용했던 것에서 비롯된 것으로, 제12비행대의 상징으로도 알려져 있었습니다. 그러나 이보다 현대적인 표식이 제12비행대의 버캐니어에 사용되었으며 엔진 흡기구 측면에 부착되어 있었습니다.

<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng của Phi đoàn số 12. Biểu tượng mô tả đầu cáo gầm gừ, một phiên bản chính xác một-tỷ-lệ-một của huy hiệu phi đoàn. Đầu cáo được chọn làm biểu tượng cho Phi đoàn số 12 vì vào năm 1926, họ là phi đoàn đầu tiên được trang bị Fairey Fox, một loại máy bay chiến đấu mạnh mẽ cho thời điểm đó và là biểu tượng tự hào mạnh mẽ cho nhóm. Tuy nhiên, dấu hiệu hiện đại hơn này được đặt trên một số máy bay tấn công Buccaneer của Phi đoàn số 12, và được đặt ở bên cạnh lỗ hút khí động cơ.

<Chinese>: 第 237 作\t战\t转\t训\t中\t队\t徽\t标
<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng của Phi đoàn OCU số 237

<English>: The emblem of No. 237 Operational Conversion Unit. No. 237 operated as a training unit, with the longest run of activity being from March 1971 to October 1991, where they flew Blackburn Buccaneers and several Hawker Hunter variants in training roles. The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.
<French>: L'emblème de l'unité de conversion opérationnelle n° 237. Le No. 237 a opéré en tant qu'unité d'entraînement, avec la plus longue période d'activité de mars 1971 à octobre 1991, où ils ont piloté des Blackburn Buccaneer et plusieurs variantes de Hawker Hunter dans des rôles d'entraînement. L'emblème représente une paire de sabres croisés derrière un chapeau académique. L'emblème était placé sur le côté des entrées d'air des Buccaneer du groupe, ainsi que sur le côté du nez de plusieurs Hawker Hunter.
<Italian>: The emblem of No. 237 Operational Conversion Unit. No. 237 operated as a training unit, with the longest run of activity being from March 1971 to October 1991, where they flew Blackburn Buccaneers and several Hawker Hunter variants in training roles. The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.
<German>: Das Emblem der No. 237 Operational Conversion Unit. No. 237 operierte als eine Trainingseinheit, mit der längsten Einsatzdauer von März 1971 bis Oktober 1991, als sie Blackburn Buccaneers und verschiedene Hawker Hunter Varianten in Trainingsrollen flogen. Das Emblem zeigt ein Paar von gekreuzten Entermessern hinter einem Doktorhut. Das Abzeichen war auf den seitlichen Triebwerkseinlässen der Buccaneers der Gruppe angebracht, und auch auf den Seiten der Nasen von einigen Hawker Hunter.
<Spanish>: Emblema de la Unidad de Conversión Operativa No. 237. El No. 237 funcionó como unidad de entrenamiento, siendo su período de actividad más largo el comprendido entre Marzo de 1971 y Octubre de 1991, en el que volaron Blackburn Buccaneers y varias variantes de Hawker Hunter en funciones de entrenamiento. El emblema muestra un par de sables cruzados detrás de una gorra académica. La marca se colocó en el lateral de las tomas de los motores de los Buccaneers del grupo, y también en el lateral del morro de varios Hawker Hunter.
<Polish>: Emblemat Jednostki Operacyjnego Przekształcenia nr 237. Eskadra nr 237 działała jako jednostka szkoleniowa, z najdłuższym okresem aktywności od marca 1971 do października 1991 roku, podczas którego latała na samolotach Blackburn Buccaneer i kilku wariantach Hawker Hunter w rolach szkoleniowych. Emblemat przedstawia parę skrzyżowanych szabli za akademicką czapką. Znak ten był umieszczony na bokach wlotów silników Buccaneerów tej grupy, a także na bokach nosa kilku samolotów Hawker Hunter.
<Czech>: The emblem of No. 237 Operational Conversion Unit. No. 237 operated as a training unit, with the longest run of activity being from March 1971 to October 1991, where they flew Blackburn Buccaneers and several Hawker Hunter variants in training roles. The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.
<Turkish>: No. 237 Operasyonel Dönüşüm Biriminin amblemi. 237 numara eğitim birimi olarak faaliyet göstermiş ve en uzun faaliyet dönemi Mart 1971'den Ekim 1991'e kadar Blackburn Buccaneers ve çeşitli Hawker Hunter varyantlarını eğitim rollerinde uçurmuştur. Amblemde akademik bir şapkanın arkasında bir çift çapraz kılıç yer almaktadır. İşaret, grubun Buccaneer'larının motor girişlerinin yan tarafına ve ayrıca birkaç Hawker Hunter'ın burun kısmına yerleştirilmiştir.
<Chinese>: 英\t国\t皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 237 作\t战\t转\t训\t中\t队 (OCU) 徽\t标。\t作\t战\t转\t训\t中\t队\t承\t担\t机\t型\t转\t换\t的\t训\t练\t任\t务，\t第 237 中\t队\t时\t间\t最\t长\t的\t任\t务\t周\t期\t从 1971 年 3 月\t持\t续\t至 1991 年 10 月，\t期\t间\t主\t要\t使\t用\t布\t莱\t克\t本\t“掠\t夺\t者”\t与\t数\t架\t霍\t克\t“猎\t人”\t系\t列\t战\t机\t进\t行\t训\t练。\t徽\t标\t主\t体\t图\t案\t为\t学\t士\t帽\t与\t后\t方\t交\t叉\t弯\t刀\t的\t组\t合，\t主\t要\t喷\t绘\t在\t中\t队\t下\t属\t“掠\t夺\t者”\t攻\t击\t机\t发\t动\t机\t进\t气\t道\t两\t侧\t与\t霍\t克\t“猎\t人”\t机\t鼻\t侧\t面\t位\t置。

No. 237 operated as a training unit, with the longest run of activity being from March 1971 to October 1991, where they flew Blackburn Buccaneers and several Hawker Hunter variants in training roles. The emblem displays a pair of crossed cutlass swords behind an academic cap. The marking was positioned on the side of the engine intakes on the Buccaneers of the group, and also on the side of the nose on several Hawker Hunters.
<HChinese>: Emblem of the 237th OCU Squadron, RAF
<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng của Đơn vị Chuyển đổi Chiến dịch số 237. Đơn vị số 237 hoạt động như một đơn vị đào tạo, với thời gian hoạt động dài nhất từ tháng 3 năm 1971 đến tháng 10 năm 1991, nơi họ bay Blackburn Buccaneers và một số biến thể của Hawker Hunter trong các vai trò đào tạo. Biểu tượng thể hiện một cặp kiếm cutlass chéo nhau phía sau một mũ học vị. Dấu hiệu này được đặt ở bên cạnh lỗ hút khí động cơ trên các máy bay Buccaneers của nhóm, và cũng ở bên cạnh mũi trên một số Hawker Hunters.

<English>: The emblem of Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 73. The unit was formed in 1959 and was initially equipped with CL-13 jet fighters, but since went on to operate a variety of aircraft including the F-4 Phantom II and MiG-29. The emblem was most commonly positioned on the tail, but aircraft such as the F-4 had it placed on the side of the fuselage behind the cockpit.
<French>: L'emblème du Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 73. L'unité a été formée en 1956 et était initialement équipé avec des chasseurs à réactions CL-13, mais depuis elle a continué à opérer sur divers avions incluant le F-4 Phantom II et le MiG-29. L'emblème était le plus souvent positionné sur la queue, mais un avion tel que le F-4 l'avait sur le côté du fuselage derrière le cockpit.
<Italian>: The emblem of Jagdgeschwader (Fighter Wing) 73. The unit was formed in 1959 and was initially equipped with CL-13 jet fighters, but since went on to operate a variety of aircraft including the F-4 Phantom II and MiG-29. The emblem was most commonly positioned on the tail, but aircraft such as the F-4 had it placed on the side of the fuselage behind the cockpit.
<German>: Das Abzeichen des Jagdgeschwaders 73. Die Einheit wurde 1959 gegründet und war zunächst mit CL-13-Düsenjägern ausgerüstet, setzte aber später eine Vielzahl von Flugzeugen ein, darunter die F-4 Phantom II und die MiG-29. Das Abzeichen befand sich in der Regel auf dem Leitwerk, bei Flugzeugen wie der F-4 war es jedoch auch seitlich am Rumpf hinter dem Cockpit angebracht.
<Spanish>: Emblema de la Jagdgeschwader (Ala de Caza) 73. La unidad se formó en 1959 y al principio estaba equipada con cazas a reacción CL-13, pero desde entonces pasó a operar una variedad de aviones, incluidos el F-4 Phantom II y el MiG-29. El emblema se colocaba normalmente en la cola, pero en aviones como el F-4 se colocaba en el lateral del fuselaje, detrás de la cabina.
<Polish>: Emblemat Jagdgeschwader 73. Jednostka została utworzona w 1959 roku i początkowo była wyposażona w myśliwce CL-13, ale później operowała różnymi samolotami, w tym F-4 Phantom II i MiG-29. Emblemat był najczęściej umieszczany na ogonie, ale samoloty takie jak F-4 miały go umieszczony na boku kadłuba za kabiną.
<Czech>: Znak Jagdgeschwader (Stíhacího křídla) 73. Jednotka byla zformována v roce 1959 a zpočátku byla vybavena proudovými stíhačkami CL-13, ale od té doby provozovala celou řadu letounů včetně F-4 Phantom II a MiG-29. Znak byl nejčastěji umístěn na ocase, ale letouny jako F-4 jej měly umístěn na boku trupu za pilotní kabinou.
<Turkish>: Jagdgeschwader (Avcı Kanadı) 73'ün amblemi. Birim 1959 yılında kurulmuş ve başlangıçta CL-13 jet avcı uçakları ile donatılmıştı, ancak daha sonra F-4 Phantom II ve MiG-29 dahil olmak üzere çeşitli uçakları kullanmaya devam etti. Amblem en yaygın olarak kuyruğa yerleştirilmiştir, ancak F-4 gibi uçaklarda kokpitin arkasındaki gövdenin yan tarafına yerleştirilmiştir.

<French>: Emblème des "Pirates du ciel", escadron n° 208

<English>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<French>: L'emblème des "Pirates du ciel", escadron n° 208. Les Buccaneers de cet escadron portaient tous une variante du drapeau pirate Jolly Roger ainsi que l'inscription "Sky Pirates" - chaque crâne variait, certains arborant une expression colérique tandis que d'autres étaient plus joviaux, cette version manque de quelques dents et semble également porter un casque d'écoute. Tous les marquages ont été placés au même endroit, juste sous l'avant du cockpit sur le côté gauche.
<Italian>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<German>: Das "Sky Pirates" (Himmelspiraten) Emblem der No. 208 Squadron. Die Buccaneers dieser Staffel trugen alle eine Abwandlung der "Jolly Roger" Piratenflagge zusammen mit der "Sky Pirates" Inschrift - Jeder Schädel war unterschiedlich, manche mit zornigen Ausdrücken, andere waren eher heiter. Dieser Version fehlen ein paar Zähne und scheint Kopfhörer zu tragen. Jede Markierung wurde an der gleichen Stelle platziert, gleich unter der Front des Cockpits auf der Backbordseite.
<Spanish>: El emblema de los "Piratas del Cielo", Escuadrón No. 208. Todos los Buccaneers de este escuadrón llevaban alguna variante de la bandera pirata del jolly roger junto con la inscripción "Piratas del Cielo" - cada calavera variaba, algunas lucían expresiones de enfado mientras que otras eran más joviales, a esta versión le faltan algunos dientes y también parece llevar auriculares. Todas las marcas estaban colocadas en el mismo lugar, justo debajo de la parte delantera de la cabina, a babor.
<Polish>: Emblemat „Sky Pirates” 208 Dywizjonu. Buccaneery tego dywizjonu miały różne wersje flagi pirackiej "jolly roger" wraz z napisem "Sky Pirates" - każda czaszka była inna, niektóre miały gniewne wyrazy, inne były bardziej wesołe. Ten konkretny emblemat ma brakujące zęby i wydaje się nosić słuchawki. Wszystkie oznaczenia były umieszczone w tym samym miejscu, tuż pod przodem kabiny po lewej stronie.
<Czech>: The "Sky Pirates" emblem, No. 208 Squadron. The Buccaneers of this squadron all wore some variation of the jolly roger pirate flag along with the "Sky Pirates" inscription — each skull varied, with some sporting angry expressions while others were more jovial, this version is missing a few teeth and also seems to be wearing headphones. All of the markings were positioned in the same place, just under the front of the cockpit on the port side.
<Turkish>: “Gökyüzü Korsanları” amblemi, No. 208 Filo. Bu filodaki Korsanların hepsi “Gökyüzü Korsanları” yazısıyla birlikte neşeli korsan bayrağının bir varyasyonunu taşıyordu - her kafatası farklıydı, bazıları kızgın ifadeler taşırken diğerleri daha neşeliydi, bu versiyonda birkaç diş eksik ve ayrıca kulaklık takıyor gibi görünüyor. Tüm işaretler aynı yere, iskele tarafındaki kokpitin ön kısmının hemen altına yerleştirilmişti.
<Chinese>: 皇\t家\t空\t军\t第 208 飞\t行\t中\t队\t“空\t中\t海\t盗”\t徽\t标。\t该\t中\t队\t下\t属\t掠\t夺\t者\t攻\t击\t机\t最\t引\t人\t瞩\t目\t的\t外\t观\t特\t征\t莫\t过\t于\t机\t身\t喷\t绘\t有\t各\t种\t样\t式\t的\t海\t盗\t旗\t以\t及\t“空\t中\t海\t盗”\t标\t语。\t海\t盗\t旗\t上\t的\t骷\t髅\t神\t态\t各\t异，\t有\t的\t面\t露\t愠\t色，\t有\t的\t神\t情\t欢\t快，\t游\t戏\t中\t的\t这\t枚\t徽\t标\t则\t少\t了\t几\t颗\t牙\t齿，\t似\t乎\t还\t戴\t着\t飞\t行\t耳\t机。\t所\t有\t海\t盗\t旗\t徽\t标\t均\t喷\t绘\t于\t座\t舱\t前\t方\t的\t左\t侧\t机\t身\t蒙\t皮\t位\t置。

<Ukrainian>: Емблема «Небесні пірати», 208-а ескадрилья. Усі пірати цієї ескадрильї носили певний варіант піратського прапора Веселого Роджера разом із написом «Небесні пірати» — кожен череп був різним, деякі мали гнівний вираз обличчя, а інші були більш веселими, у цій версії бракує кількох зубів, а також, як видно він в навушниках. Усі позначки були розташовані в одному місці, прямо під передньою частиною кабіни з лівого борту.

<Korean>: 제208비행대가 사용한 "Sky Pirates" 엠블럼입니다. 이 비행대에서 버캐니어를 조종했던 조종사들은, “Sky Priates(하늘의 해적)” 이라는 해적 깃발이 그려진 데칼을 사용했는데, 각 해골의 모습 또한 다양했다고 합니다. 본 데칼은 화난 표정을 가지고 있지만 다른 표정들의 경우 더 유쾌한 모습을 가지고 있었습니다. 이 버전은 몇 개의 치아가 빠진 상태로 헤드폰을 착용한 모습을 하고 있습니다. 이러한 데칼은 모두 조종석 좌측 아래 동체에 위치해 있었습니다.

<Vietnamese>: Biểu tượng "Hải tặc bầu trời" của Phi đoàn số 208. Những chiếc Buccaneers của phi đoàn này đều mang một phiên bản nào đó của lá cờ cướp biển jolly roger cùng với dòng chữ "Sky Pirates" - mỗi bộ hài cốt đều khác nhau, một số mang vẻ mặt tức giận trong khi những cái khác lại vui vẻ hơn, phiên bản này thiếu vài chiếc răng và cũng dường như đang đeo tai nghe. Tất cả các dấu hiệu đều được đặt ở cùng một vị trí, ngay dưới phía trước của buồng lái ở phía bên trái.
